9. A signal decoding method for performing arithmetic decoding and other decoding operations, wherein the arithmetic decoding is performed using probability information table which comprises transition states each assigned a table address, the method comprising:
having as inputs a coded signal, a reference value and at least one parameter, the at least one parameter relating to at least one of the other decoding operations;
deriving a table address of an initial state in the table, using the reference value and the at least one parameter, the table address being a function of the reference value and the at least one parameter;
performing the arithmetic decoding on the coded signal, using the initial state addressed by the table address.

17. A signal encoding method for performing arithmetic coding and other encoding operation, wherein the arithmetic coding is performed using probability information, the method comprising:
analyzing at least a part of target signal to determine an initial value of the probability information;
performing the arithmetic coding on the at least a part of target signal, using the initial value of the probability information;
determining a reference value, the initial value of the probability information being a function of the reference value and at least one parameter, the at least one parameter relating to at least one of the other encoding operations; and
composing a header which comprises the reference value and the at least one parameter.

18. A signal encoding apparatus which performs arithmetic coding and other encoding operations, wherein the arithmetic coding is performed using probability information, the apparatus comprising:
an analyzer configured to analyze at least a part of target signal to determine an initial value of the probability information;
an arithmetic coding engine configured to perform the arithmetic coding on the at least a part of target signal, using the initial value of the probability information;
a reference value generator configured to determine a reference value, the initial value of the probability information being a function of the reference value and at least one parameter, the at least one parameter relating to at least one of the other encoding operations; and
a header generator configured to compose a header which comprises the reference value and the at least one parameter.

19. A signal encoding method for performing arithmetic coding and other encoding operations, wherein the arithmetic coding is performed using a probability information table which comprises transition states each assigned a table address, the method comprising:
analyzing at least a part of target signal to determine an initial state in the table;
performing the arithmetic coding on the at least a part of target signal, using the initial state;
determining a reference value, a table address of the initial state in the table being a function of the reference value and at least one parameter, the at least one parameter relating to the at least one of the other encoding operations; and
composing a header which comprises the reference value and the at least one parameter.

20. A signal encoding apparatus which performs arithmetic coding and other encoding operations, wherein the arithmetic coding is performed using a probability information table which comprises transition states each assigned a table address, the apparatus comprising:
an analyzer configured to analyze at least a part of target signal to determine an initial state in the table;
an arithmetic coding engine configured to perform the arithmetic coding on the at least a part of target signal, using the initial state;
a reference value generator configured to determine a reference value, a table address of the initial state in the table being a function of the reference value and at least one parameter, the at least one parameter relating to at least one of the encoding operations; and
a header generator configured to compose a header which comprises the reference value and the at least one parameter.
